Hynix, LG, Samsung, SK Telecom, STX: South Korea Equity Preview

-- B y   J u n   Y a n g
-- 
2011-09-19T23:31:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/hynix-lg-samsung-sk-telecom-stx-south-korea-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise. The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  fell 1 percent to 1,820.94.  Hynix Semiconductor Inc. (000660 KS): The South Korean
chipmaker and Micron Technology Inc. colluded to drive computer
memory chips designed by Rambus Inc. out of the market, a lawyer
for Rambus told a jury yesterday. The chip manufacturers deny
the claims. The stock dropped 4.1 percent to 21,000 won.  LG Electronics Inc. (066570)  (066570 KS): The company is seeking to
triple its solar-panel manufacturing capacity by 2013 to become
one of the 10 biggest producers, Handelsblatt reported, citing
Michael Harre, head of LG’s European solar unit. The company
also wants to expand into silicon output, the raw material for
photovoltaic products, Handelsblatt said. The stock fell 0.3
percent to 62,200 won.  Samsung Electronics Co. (005930 KS): The company is
considering moving its liquid-crystal display production to
 China , MoneyToday reported, citing industry sources that it
didn’t identify. The world’s largest LCD maker rose 1.3 percent
to 808,000 won.  SK Telecom co. (017670 KS): The mobile-phone operator was
left as the only suitor to bid for a 20 percent stake in  Hynix
Semiconductor Inc. (000660)  as STX Group dropped out of the competition.
South Korea’s largest mobile-phone carrier dropped 3.5 percent
to 154,000 won, while STX Corp. (011810 KS), which was leading
the group’s bid for Hynix, gained 3.8 percent to 16,300 won.  000660 KS <Equity>
